  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I become a sub inspector in delhi police after graduation?",
  "response": "To become a **Sub-Inspector (SI)** in the **Delhi Police** after graduation, you need to follow a structured process. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Eligibility Criteria**\n   - **Nationality**: Indian citizen.\n   - **Age Limit**: Typically between 20 to 25 years (varies based on category and notifications). Relaxation is given for reserved categories as per government norms.\n   - **Educational Qualification**:\n     - Bachelor\u2019s degree from a recognized university.\n     - Some notifications may specify additional requirements (e.g., specific subjects or skills).\n   - **Physical Standards**:\n     - **Height**: Male (170 cm), Female (157 cm). Relaxation for certain categories.\n     - **Chest** (for males only): 81-85 cm (minimum expansion of 5 cm).\n   - **Medical Fitness**: Must meet the medical standards set by Delhi Police.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Recruitment Process**\n   The recruitment for Sub-Inspector in Delhi Police is conducted through the **Staff Selection Commission (SSC)** under the **Central Armed Police Forces (CAPF)** or through **Delhi Police\u2019s own recruitment notifications**. Follow these steps:\n\n#### **Step 1: Apply for the Exam**\n   - Keep an eye on the official notifications from **SSC** (**ssc.nic.in**) or **Delhi Police** (**delhipolice.nic.in**).\n   - Fill out the online application form when the notification is released.\n   - Pay the application fee (if applicable).\n\n#### **Step 2: Written Examination**\n   - The written exam typically includes subjects like:\n     - General Intelligence & Reasoning\n     - General Knowledge & Awareness\n     - Quantitative Aptitude\n     - English Language & Comprehension\n   - The exam pattern and syllabus may vary based on the notification.\n\n#### **Step 3: Physical Efficiency Test (PET) & Physical Standard Test (PST)**\n   - Candidates must qualify in physical tests like:\n     - **Race**: Male (1.6 km in 6.5 minutes), Female (800 meters in 4 minutes).\n     - Long Jump, High Jump, etc.\n   - Physical measurements for height, chest, and weight are also checked.\n\n#### **Step 4: Medical Examination**\n   - Candidates must pass a medical test to ensure they are fit for the role.\n\n#### **Step 5: Document Verification**\n   - Original documents are verified (educational certificates, age proof, caste certificate, etc.).\n\n#### **Step 6: Final Selection**\n   - Based on the performance in the written exam, PET/PST, and medical test, a merit list is prepared.\n   - Selected candidates undergo training at Delhi Police Training Schools.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Prepare Effectively**\n   - Study the syllabus and exam pattern thoroughly.\n   - Practice previous years\u2019 question papers and mock tests.\n   - Improve your physical fitness for the PET/PST.\n   - Stay updated with current affairs and general knowledge.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Training**\n   - Once selected, you will undergo rigorous training at Delhi Police Training Schools.\n   - Training includes physical, technical, and theoretical components.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Career Growth**\n   - After becoming a Sub-Inspector, you can advance through promotions to higher ranks like Inspector, Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP), etc.\n\n---\n\n### Important Links\n- **SSC Official Website**: [ssc.nic.in](https://ssc.nic.in)\n- **Delhi Police Recruitment**: [delhipolice.nic.in](https://delhipolice.nic.in)\n\nStay updated with notifications and prepare diligently to achieve your goal. Good luck! \ud83d\udea8",
  "temperature": 1.0,
